definition.value: An anionic phospholipid obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of any 1-acyl-2-decanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate; major species at pH 7.3.
A saturated fatty acyl-CoA(4-) oxoanion arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of hexacosanoyl-CoA; the major species at pH 7.3.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate in which the acyl group at position 1 is unspecified while that at position 2 is specified as palmitoyl (hexadecanoyl).
A carbohydrate acid derivative anion obtained by deprotonation of both carboxy groups of (S)-malyl N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosaminide; major species at pH 7.3.
A carbohydrate acid derivative anion obtained by deprotonation of both carboxy groups and protonation of the amino group of (S)-malyl alpha-D-glucosaminide; major species at pH 7.3.
An anionic phospholipid obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of any 2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-D-myo-inositol; major species at pH 7.3.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate in which the acyl group at position 1 is unspecified while that at position 2 is specified as myristoyl (tetradecanoyl).
An anionic phospholipid obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of any 1-acyl-2-hexadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-1D-myo-inositol; major species at pH 7.3.
An anionic phospholipid obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of any 1-hexadecanoyl-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-1D-myo-inositol; major species at pH 7.3.
A carbohydrate acid derivative anion obtained by deprotonation of both carboxy groups and protonation of the amino group of bacillithiol; major species at pH 7.3.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate in which the acyl group at position 1 is unspecified while that at position 2 is specified as lauroyl (dodecanoyl).
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate in which the acyl group at position 1 is unspecified while that at position 2 is specified as decanoyl

A triply-charged organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the free phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of 6-O-(1-glycerylphospho)-N-acetyl-beta-D-mannosaminyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl undecaprenyl diphosphate; major species at pH 7.3.
An N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosaminide having (S)-malyl as the anomeric substituent.
An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of diacetylchitobiose-6-phosphate; major species at pH 7.3.
An anionic C20 phospholipid obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups and protonation of the amino group of C20 phytosphingosine 1-phosphate; major species at pH 7.3.
A cationic sphingoid that is the conjugate acid of C20 phytosphingosine, obtained by protonation of the primary amino function; major species at pH 7.3.
The organophosphate oxoanion resulting from the addition of a proton to the amino group and the removal of the two acidic protons from the phosphate group of C20 sphinganine 1-phosphate.
A cationic sphingoid obtained by protonation of the amino group of C20 sphinganine; major species at pH 7.3.
A D-glucosaminide having (S)-malyl as the anomeric substituent and alpha-configuration at the anomeric centre.
A 1-phosphatidyl-D-myo-inositol in which the acyl group at position 1 is unspecified while that at position 2 is specified as palmitoyl (hexadecanoyl).
A 1-phosphatidyl-D-myo-inositol in which the acyl group at position 1 is specified as palmitoyl (hexadecanoyl) while that at position 2 is unspecified.
An alpha-amino-acid residue derived from O-(pantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine.

A polyprenyl phospho oligosaccharide where 6-O-(1-glycerylphospho)-N-acetyl-beta-D-mannosaminyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl comprises the oligosaccharide component and the polyprenyl chain consists of eleven prenyl units.
A diketone that is bornane bearing two oxo substituents at positions 2 and 6.

A hydroxy monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of [(1S)-4-hydroxy-2,2,3-trimethylcyclopent-3-enyl]acetic acid, arising from deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A serine derivative in which L-serine is substituted on oxygen by a pantetheine 4'-phosphate group.
A disaccharide phosphate that is diacetylchitobiose substituted at position 6' by a phospho group.
An amino-acid residue carrying an overall negative charge.
A 5-hydroxy monocarboxylic acid that is acetic acid in which one of the methyl hydrogens is substituted by a 4-hydroxy-2,2,3-trimethylcyclopent-3-enyl group (the S-enantiomer).
An acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of [(1R)-2,2,3-trimethyl-5-oxocyclopent-3-en-1-yl]acetic acid.
A member of the class of  benzamides obtained by formal condensation of the two primary amino groups of spemidine with the carboxy groups from two molecules of 2,5-dihydroxybenzoic acid.
A perylene that consists of dihydroxyperylene-3,9-dione bering hydroxy groups at positions 4 and 10.
A 2-aminoicosane-1,3-diol having (2S,3R)-configuration.
An aminodiol that is icosane bearing two hydroxy substituents at positions 1 and 3 as well as an amino substituent at position 2.
2-Oxohex-3-enedioate in which the C=C double bond has E configuration; principal microspecies at pH 7.3.
Any substance that causes disturbance to organisms by chemical reaction or other activity on the molecular scale, when a sufficient quantity is absorbed by the organism.
A sphingoid that is C20 sphinganine bearing an additional 4R-hydroxy substituent.
Any compound that inhibits cell division (mitosis).

A drug used to treat or prevent infections caused by Mycobacteria, a genus of actinobacteria. Aerobic and nonmotile, members of the genus include the pathogens responsible for causing tuberculosis and leprosy.
A dihydroceramide in which the ceramide acyl group is specified as acetyl.
An antiparasitic drug which is effective against Apicomplexan parasites in the genus Plasmodium. The genus contains over 200 species and includes those responsible for malaria.
An anionic phospholipid obtained by deprotonation of the free phosphate OH group of any inositol phosphoceramide; major species at pH 7.3.
The phosphosphingolipid that is the phosphate ester of C20 sphinganine.
A phosphosphingolipid that is C20 phytosphingosine bearing a phospho group at position 1.
An  EC 2.3.1.* (acyltransferase transferring other than amino-acyl group) inhibitor that interferes with the action of diacylglycerol O-acyltransferase (EC 2.3.1.20).
An EC 6.5.1.* (DNA/RNA repair enzymes) inhibitor that interferes with the action of DNA ligase (ATP), EC 6.5.1.1.
Benzoic acid substituted with hydroxy groups at C-3 and -4 and with a polyprenyl chain of unspecified length at C-5.
An EC 3.4.21.* (serine endopeptidase) inhibitor that interferes with the activity of leukocyte elastase (EC 3.4.21.37).
